1
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,880
<i>The flash drive in your office</i>

2
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:42,360
<i>has been stolen.</i>

3
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:45,680
The flash drive is linked
to each member's access code.

4
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:48,120
But more than the data, it's the mask.

5
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,480
Who are you really working for?

6
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:01,720
Punlop.

7
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:17,720
You asked to live a normal life,

8
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,520
and I already allowed it.

9
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,720
I'll enter the code
for the person who didn't show up,

10
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:58,200
so you can go in and hear
Fire Phoenix's crimes.

11
00:05:58,280 --> 00:06:00,440
Then think of a way to destroy them.

12
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,880
<i>And whenever</i>

13
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,000
you can forgive me,

14
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,440
call me again.

15
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,240
I want to laugh with you all.

16
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,280
Mom.

17
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:05,000
Someone tweeted
that 3C Corp. made a pathogen.

18
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:10,360
My team posted the tweet
about the pathogen.

19
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:13,760
This will actually work, right?

20
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,440
At least,

21
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:18,120
it should slow down
the spread of the pathogen a bit.

22
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,760
Cancel the meeting.

23
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,360
Wait!

24
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,240
Why didn't you get the email
like the rest of us?

25
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,640
Mom.

26
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:57,040
I need the medicine.

27
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:00,520
If you want medicine,
you have to answer my question.

28
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:05,040
Who did you order
to tweet about the pathogen?

29
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,360
I didn't order anyone.

30
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,240
I've taught you since you were little.

31
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,480
Never lie where people can catch you.

32
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,840
Mom, I didn't do it.

33
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:24,240
Please don't kill me.

34
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,720
Mom…

35
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,920
Think carefully before you answer.

36
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:36,160
Otherwise, your life

37
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:39,720
will keep slipping away.

38
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,440
Just a little more,

39
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,240
and I'll get to Damon.

40
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:17,120
The news about the pathogen
stopped everything.

41
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,880
I didn't think
it would halt the meetings too.

42
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,880
I just wanted the news about the pathogen

43
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,680
to drop the 3C-Coin price, that's all.

44
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,080
You did well, Sun.

45
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,720
I need another chance
to get close to Damon.

46
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,400
They probably won't dare
do anything else for now.

47
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:35,320
At least let's find Rin first.

48
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:37,000
Khanin.

49
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:40,560
Haven't you found any leads at all?

50
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:29,800
Hey, Sun.

51
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:33,920
The 3C-Coin just spiked green
for a moment.

52
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:36,800
Okay, keep working.

53
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,000
Bye.

54
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,840
Whoa!

55
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:44,640
Rin!

56
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:49,720
Rin.

57
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:09,680
Rin.

58
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:11,440
Go stay with Mr. Taiga.

59
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:13,440
It's not safe for you here.

60
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,160
Mr. Taiga cares about you.

61
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,840
He won't let anything happen to you.

62
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:19,880
Call him to come get you.

63
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,120
Aru.

64
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:23,120
Please.

65
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,880
If anyone is near me,
they'll all be in danger.

66
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:32,800
Okay, I won't tell anyone.

67
00:14:58,880 --> 00:14:59,960
Rin has escaped.

68
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,360
Be careful around 3C Corp. too.

69
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:04,920
Got it. I'll be careful.

70
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:11,960
Who is it?

71
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:12,960
It's me, Mom.

72
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:16,840
Are you okay?

73
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:18,840
You look tense.

74
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:21,840
I'm fine.

75
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:24,560
I love you, Mom.

76
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,720
I love you the most.

77
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,800
I love you too.

78
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,280
I love you so much

79
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:35,760
that I've prepared everything for you.

80
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,680
Because I know

81
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,320
what my child lacks.

82
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,160
Remember this.

83
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:46,680
We must take revenge on everyone
who looks down on us.

84
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:49,400
Make them bow to us.

85
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,120
Life is a battle.

86
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,880
Only the strong can be victorious.

87
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:20,040
<i>Have you heard that 3C Corp.</i>
<i>is planning a big event?</i>

88
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,960
Nunnapat is organizing a major event

89
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:24,840
to promote both the app and the coin.

90
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,720
She's rushing the event,

91
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:28,280
promoting it to draw a big crowd.

92
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:29,280
Ratee.

93
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:32,520
Tell me all the details about the event.

94
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,160
This is going to be bad, right?

95
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:38,760
3C Corp. is planning something bad,
like releasing a pathogen.

96
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:40,560
Most likely.

97
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,800
Rin, are you okay?

98
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,880
Hey, are you feeling unwell?

99
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:04,040
The medicine you took,
it's really fine, right?

100
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,520
Yeah, I'm fine.

101
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:08,280
Look, the dark spots are gone.

102
00:17:13,839 --> 00:17:15,640
That's a relief.

103
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:18,079
It's an experimental drug.

104
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:20,200
Honestly, I'm worried
about the side effects.

105
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:24,240
I have no idea what it might do
to your body long-term.

106
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,120
Aru.

107
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,440
Don't tell Mr. Taiga.

108
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:35,800
Sun is smashing the 3C-Coin.

109
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,160
So what's our next move?

110
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:46,880
Have you been able to find Dhammatat yet?

111
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,920
He's completely disappeared.

112
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:51,960
Not yet.

113
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:53,840
He's still in hiding.

114
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:59,120
I don't want anything to happen to him.

115
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:02,400
Fire Phoenix might be hunting him.

116
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:04,280
They'll go after everyone

117
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:05,760
before the pathogen event.

118
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:09,200
Fire Phoenix is releasing a pathogen
at their own event?

119
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,480
Isn't that too risky?

120
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:12,720
They're bold enough to do it.

121
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,320
They've layered their plans carefully.

122
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,960
How would they

123
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:21,200
expose people to the pathogen?

124
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:24,640
Inhalation? Ingestion?

125
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:28,960
Would the symptoms be like Rin's,
or even worse?

126
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:13,320
Thank you.

127
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:22,680
<i>Some people just can't stay apart</i>

128
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:25,760
<i>because there's an enormous attraction</i>
<i>between them.</i>

129
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:27,640
<i>Do you believe that?</i>

130
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:30,240
<i>I don't.</i>

131
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,440
<i>I'm not an artist.</i>

132
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:41,560
<i>Don't let anything happen to you, Rin.</i>
<i>Wait for me</i>

133
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,440
<i>until I come back for you.</i>

134
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,240
Here.

135
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:33,640
We're going to cancel
the press conference for the Hi app.

136
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,000
Mom!

137
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:37,680
Lately, 3C Corp.
has only had bad news coming out.

138
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,640
But we should use the media
to tell the truth.

139
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:43,720
So people won't misunderstand.

140
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,960
Mr. Taiga, you want to hold the event?

141
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,640
I think that even in bad luck,

142
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:51,240
we can turn it into opportunity.

143
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,600
In today's society,

144
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:55,920
silence means you admit guilt.

145
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:59,200
If that's not the case,
you have to respond immediately.

146
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:02,920
People will get it, everything's clear,
it's settled, and they'll move on.

147
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:05,480
That's true, Mom.

148
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:09,280
We can use the media
to respond to those crazy tweets.

149
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:12,200
I think, if we're going to hold the event,

150
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:15,480
we have to look at the big picture,
whether it's worth the cost.

151
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:18,120
If it's just promoting the app
and correcting the news,

152
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:20,600
without anything new to surprise people,

153
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:22,920
the value is low.

154
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,400
If the media presses about the pathogen,

155
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:27,480
3C Corp. will make headlines again.

156
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:31,040
And this time, our coin will plummet.

157
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:34,840
Let's do it this way.

158
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:07,960
I just don't want to be someone
who fails at everything.

159
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:12,200
No results, no recognition.

160
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:17,240
This is my chance

161
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,840
to show everyone

162
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:23,040
that even without Dad

163
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:25,440
or Te,

164
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:28,960
I'm still here.

165
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,240
I know

166
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,960
you can do great things, Ms. Nun.

167
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:44,840
I believe that one day

168
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:46,440
everyone will see.

169
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:50,880
Diamonds shine brightest in the dark

170
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:52,840
because a diamond isn't just a pebble.

171
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:06,520
Thank you so much, Mr. Taiga,

172
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:08,880
for believing in me.

173
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:22,080
I'll be a good friend to you.

174
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:24,840
And if it's more than friendship,

175
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:27,240
what should I do?

176
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:50,240
Even if you say no,

177
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:53,120
I'll make it happen.

178
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,360
Where are you going?

179
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:15,760
3C Corp.

180
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:21,800
Rin, listen.

181
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:25,560
Mr. Naruban isn't at 3C Corp. anymore.

182
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:28,360
It's not the same as before.

183
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:32,240
Nothing about this situation is reliable.

184
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:37,920
I think you should stay put
and watch for now. Okay?

185
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:41,920
At least wait
until you've fully recovered.

186
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:44,960
Don't go out in your current state.

187
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:49,960
- I'm--
- You're okay?

188
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:00,560
It's fine to be weak sometimes, Rin.

189
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,880
Be weak so you can keep moving,

190
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:07,080
not pretend to be strong

191
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:09,600
when you're actually exhausted.

192
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:14,640
I have to handle everything myself.

193
00:26:15,160 --> 00:26:16,400
Handle what?

194
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:19,320
Tell me. I'll help you.

195
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:22,080
No one can help.

196
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:24,400
I have to do it myself.

197
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:28,360
I have to find the truth on my own.

198
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,800
I can endure anything.

199
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:47,400
I can endure all the pain.

200
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:51,200
Endure it for whom?

201
00:26:52,120 --> 00:26:53,640
For yourself,

202
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:55,320
Mr. Taiga,

203
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:57,720
or Mr. Naruban?

204
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:13,320
No.

205
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:16,280
They killed…

206
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:18,840
No.

207
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:21,040
Prin.

208
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:23,520
No.

209
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,600
They killed…

210
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:30,440
They killed…

211
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:32,760
Mr. Naruban is rambling something.

212
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:35,280
Get closer and hear what he's saying.

213
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:37,640
They…

214
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:39,160
They killed Prin!

215
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:40,240
- They killed Prin!
- Ah!

216
00:27:41,720 --> 00:27:43,800
What happened? Why did you scream?

217
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:48,720
No.

218
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:54,240
He has fallen asleep.

219
00:27:58,640 --> 00:27:59,600
Ugh.

220
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:07,200
I endure to take my revenge.

221
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,200
Who are you after?

222
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:13,880
Tell me.

223
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:17,960
Do you remember?

224
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:22,800
If there's no sun,

225
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:26,520
I'll be your sunshine.

226
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,400
Aru.

227
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,080
If there's no sun,

228
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:34,320
I'll be your sunshine.

229
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,280
Sound familiar?

230
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:43,560
Stop lying, Lee!

231
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:51,920
You've been there for me the whole time,

232
00:28:52,520 --> 00:28:54,600
from the first day I got out of prison.

233
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:59,960
When I was completely depressed,

234
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:03,480
my life felt hopeless.

235
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:07,280
It's dark.

236
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:10,440
It's all dark.

237
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:15,200
But you did what you promised.

238
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:21,160
You became my light.

239
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,880
You've known for a long time, Aru?

240
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:40,280
Yes.

241
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:44,920
But I pretended not to know.

242
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:50,880
I wanted to see
how long you could hide it from me.

243
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:00,600
But don't forget.

244
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:07,200
We're the light in each other's lives.

245
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:14,120
The sky gets dark,

246
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:17,640
so the stars shine.

247
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:21,360
The rain falls,

248
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:24,760
so we can see the rainbow.

249
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:30,520
Everything happens for each other.

250
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:34,680
Don't carry the burden alone anymore, Lee.

251
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:38,080
Now that I see you,

252
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:41,360
let me take the pain for you.

253
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:57,880
I beg you.

254
00:31:01,320 --> 00:31:03,120
Take care of yourself first.

255
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:09,520
I don't want to lose a friend again.

256
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:25,440
I don't have much time left, Aru.

257
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:33,120
I think…

258
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:37,360
the effects of the anti-pathogen drug,

259
00:31:38,760 --> 00:31:40,720
it's changing my body.

260
00:31:43,520 --> 00:31:44,760
I'm exhausted.

261
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:49,160
My gums are swollen, my mouth is bleeding.

262
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,240
My whole body aches,

263
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:58,160
even down to my bones.

264
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,440
The symptoms feel like…

265
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:07,800
Cancer?

266
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:10,760
I noticed and I searched.

267
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:13,120
The symptoms match quite a few things.

268
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:15,440
It looks…

269
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:18,600
a lot like early-stage cancer.

270
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:21,360
Is Rin being treated yet?

271
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:23,880
I don't think so.

272
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,520
Rin's hiding everything.

273
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:40,400
Keep this a secret.

274
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:46,640
Don't let anyone know
what's wrong with me.

275
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:51,480
I'm close to finding the person
who killed my father.

276
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:56,800
Wherever they're hiding, I'll find them.

277
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:59,080
You're going to 3C Corp.

278
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:02,280
Is the person
who killed your father there?

279
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:10,680
I love you, Aru.

280
00:33:12,600 --> 00:33:14,240
I want you to know as little as possible.

281
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:15,800
So you'll be safe.

282
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:31,040
Don't waver.

283
00:35:31,960 --> 00:35:34,240
Don't lose your resolve
because of Rin, Taiga.

284
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:53,680
Here.

285
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:55,760
The second-hand one you asked me to find.

286
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:57,080
Thanks.

287
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:25,920
I'm right here, in case you need any help.

288
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:52,200
NARUBAN'S FAMILY, CEO 3C

289
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:14,440
Since when have you
been close to Mr. Taiga?

290
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:16,160
We're not close.

291
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:18,440
If you lie again, I'll fire you.

292
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,520
Answer me.

293
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:27,560
Being the boss doesn't mean
you can control everything I do.

294
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:32,080
Wait.

295
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:37,280
Let go.

296
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:38,120
Nun!

297
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:43,120
If all you think about are silly,

298
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:45,040
empty-headed things,

299
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:47,960
don't tell anyone you're my child.

300
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:49,320
Now, leave!

301
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:22,440
I'm fine.

302
00:38:41,040 --> 00:38:42,880
You don't have to endure everything.

303
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:46,680
You can fight back if something's wrong.

304
00:38:47,720 --> 00:38:50,160
You can cry if you need to let it out.

305
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:54,080
Some people

306
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:56,720
don't show their tears

307
00:38:58,200 --> 00:38:59,960
because they all flow inward.

308
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:12,000
I've been a terrible father.

309
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:15,720
I've never listened
to what my children needed.

310
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:20,080
But this is my training.

311
00:39:21,240 --> 00:39:22,560
My children must be strong,

312
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:26,080
survive on their own when I'm gone.

313
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:31,560
My dad said that to me before.

314
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:40,040
I'm sorry for my daughter's foolishness.

315
00:39:44,160 --> 00:39:46,520
Go back now, Rin. Don't wait.

316
00:39:47,040 --> 00:39:48,720
I'll stay and work.

317
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:50,800
Okay.

318
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:09,840
NARUBAN'S FAMILY, CEO 3C

319
00:40:17,680 --> 00:40:18,640
Hey.

320
00:40:19,520 --> 00:40:20,600
Rin!

321
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:26,720
Have you managed to get any sleep?

322
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:29,920
Aru, I want to see Mr. Naruban.

323
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:32,200
You can't. It's too risky.

324
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:36,000
I'm not afraid. I have to see Mr. Naruban.

325
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:37,680
Why?

326
00:40:37,760 --> 00:40:40,120
He might be waiting
for someone to help him.

327
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:55,920
Where's Mr. Naruban?

328
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:59,480
If it's about work, you can talk to me.

329
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:02,200
Mr. Naruban's unwell,
so I'm taking care of things here.

330
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,880
Did he ask you to do that?

331
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:07,760
Mr. Naruban and I are two halves
of the same whole.

332
00:41:07,840 --> 00:41:09,720
Whatever he thinks or plans,

333
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:11,080
I know it all.

334
00:41:17,080 --> 00:41:19,240
This is Mr. Punlop, my assistant.

335
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:31,840
Hello.

336
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:33,480
Ms. Nunnapat.

337
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:39,920
Mr. Punlop will be helping out here.

338
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:42,160
Helping with what?

339
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:44,360
Executive Secretary to the CEO.

340
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:48,240
That's a fast promotion.

341
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:49,880
All thanks to my abilities.

342
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:52,120
Ms. Ratee, do you have a problem?

343
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:54,000
What do you want
to discuss about 3C Corp.?

344
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:59,080
I want to call a meeting.
I want things to be formal.

345
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:01,680
If Mr. Naruban
can't run the operations fully,

346
00:42:02,240 --> 00:42:04,280
we should select a new executive.

347
00:42:04,360 --> 00:42:05,560
Oh.

348
00:42:05,640 --> 00:42:08,240
That's rushing things.
Do you have an ulterior motive?

349
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:11,080
My family are investors,

350
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:12,920
not speculators.

351
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,520
Whatever we do,
it has to be certain and clear.

352
00:42:17,280 --> 00:42:18,920
Let's schedule the meeting quickly.

353
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:21,920
Even an executive no one acknowledges

354
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:24,080
can make the stock drop.

355
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:30,680
This is a massive corporate interest,

356
00:42:31,200 --> 00:42:34,880
not some petty family inheritance.

357
00:42:47,600 --> 00:42:49,240
You should have told me first

358
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:51,720
about bringing an outsider
into the company.

359
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:03,240
Your daughter isn't happy
that I'm standing here.

360
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:04,400
Hm.

361
00:43:04,960 --> 00:43:08,480
Eventually, Nun will realize
that you came to help save 3C Corp.

362
00:43:09,480 --> 00:43:12,760
And everyone will have to accept me
as the new chairperson.

363
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:17,360
Thank you so much

364
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:20,200
for resigning from the police for me.

365
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:24,960
I didn't lose anything.
I'd do anything for you.

366
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:31,200
Shareholding-wise, you must
not let Ratee hold more than 30%.

367
00:43:31,800 --> 00:43:34,280
If she brings in other investors,

368
00:43:34,920 --> 00:43:36,560
your chairperson seat will be in trouble.

369
00:43:40,280 --> 00:43:41,400
She's pushing

370
00:43:41,920 --> 00:43:44,600
because she wants 3C Corp.
under her control.

371
00:43:45,560 --> 00:43:48,080
But more importantly,
she's friends with Taiga.

372
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:51,960
Not just ordinary friends.

373
00:43:52,040 --> 00:43:53,840
They shared a private connection overseas.

374
00:43:54,440 --> 00:43:56,400
Neither Ratee nor Taiga

375
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:58,240
can be trusted, right?

376
00:43:58,320 --> 00:44:02,080
Don't worry. I'll handle both of them.

377
00:44:11,280 --> 00:44:12,440
I'm busy.

378
00:44:12,960 --> 00:44:13,960
I've got business.

379
00:44:21,520 --> 00:44:23,240
What business? Let me join.

380
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:29,440
I have my own work.

381
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:33,600
Wait.

382
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:38,320
I have something to ask you, Mr. Taiga.

383
00:44:43,200 --> 00:44:45,960
Ratee, I need to discuss something.

384
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:49,200
Taiga, you can't do this to me.

385
00:44:49,280 --> 00:44:50,480
Ratee.

386
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:12,160
I want you to help with Te.

387
00:45:16,240 --> 00:45:18,120
Why is Punlop targeting you?

388
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:19,920
Can you just leave me alone? Let go!

389
00:45:24,720 --> 00:45:25,800
<i>Tell me the truth.</i>

390
00:45:25,880 --> 00:45:27,600
How is 3C Corp. planning
to release the pathogen?

391
00:45:28,360 --> 00:45:32,040
Punlop killed your father.

392
00:45:34,800 --> 00:45:36,920
Remember this, if Rin ever finds out,

393
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:37,840
you're dead!

394
00:46:08,680 --> 00:46:10,600
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
